# Cursor Rules — sajalmia381.github.io

## Stack
- Angular 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Angular Material
- Single-page portfolio/resume app deployed to GitHub Pages

## Commands
- `npm start` — dev server on http://localhost:4400
- `npm run build` — production build → `docs/` (not `dist/`)
- `npm test` — Karma/Jasmine unit tests
- `npm run prettier` — format all source files

## Architecture rules
- Each feature follows three layers: API → State → Facade
- Components talk ONLY to the Facade — never to API or State directly
- `HomeApi` makes HTTP calls; `HomeState` holds BehaviorSubject observables; `HomeFacade` coordinates both
- All components use the `mia-` selector prefix

## Path aliases
- `@shared/*` → `src/app/shared/*` (animations, ScrollService)
- `@package/*` → `src/app/package/*` (APP_ENV token, IEnv interface)
- Always use aliases, never relative paths crossing feature boundaries

## Animations
- Custom library in `src/app/shared/animations/` — animate.css-inspired Angular factories
- Import named factories from `@shared/animations`, register in component `animations: []` with an anchor string

## Formatting
- Prettier enforced via husky pre-commit hook
- 140-char print width, double quotes, trailing commas (ES5)
- Run `npm run prettier` before committing if bypassing the hook

## Code style
- No comments unless the WHY is non-obvious
- No unused variables, no dead code
- TypeScript strict mode — no implicit any
- External data (blog posts, portfolio items) comes from WordPress REST API via `HomeApi`
